These aren't really dvds. you have to go into the iso folder and click start here

#  When connecting to another BitTorrent client, the requesting client will first try port 6881, then 6882, and so on. However, if the computer is on a firewalled network, the incoming request may not reach these ports. On the other hand, if these requests succeed, the accepting client will be able to download faster.

# Firewalls can block nearly all of the ports used by P2P clients. To ensure the BitTorrent ports are made available to requesting clients, a home router or firewall can be manually configured to accept them. Most home routers possess a feature called "Port Range Forwarding" to do this. This feature allows the administer to tell the firewall where traffic for a given port number should be directed.

If your speeds are slow do the above.

I've seeded this to a ratio of 0.9 during the DL and will continue until... well whatever it get's to for the next couple of weeks.

This collection shows exactly the type of photoshop skills you actually WANT to learn rather than what you usually get from so-called "Training DVD's" i.e. "This is what I can do as a photoshop expert, aren't you jealous" kind of tutorial.

During the last couple of years I have used TPB to update my version of photoshop but, with my level of skill, being self-taught as I am, I may as well have just used the GIMP.

What I did when DL'ing this, was to set the priority to each DVD in order so I was able to watch a DVD as I was still downloading. By the time the full set had downloaded I had managed to follow the first DVD to the point where I had produced a piece of work which surpassed, not only my previous efforts, but had even surpassed my wildest expectations. 

I've yet to see a training set as in-depth or as relevant to a novices needs as this. 

Thank you, thank you and thrice and more thank you to themodest and all seeders who have contributed to me acquiring this, quite frankly, awesome collection.

So, if you download this, don't be selfish and share.

I mean, it even takes you through a step-by-step tutorial of CG paiting for chrissakes!!! WHAT MORE CAN YOU ASK!!!!

There is no use in cursing the idiots out there to seed.  There are three types of users here on piratebay:

1st:  The n00bs, these are the people new to torrenting and don't know crap about bandwidth usages.  They never usually cap there upload limits.  I love these guys.

2nd:  Ignorant bastards, these are the people that are not n00bs, but are worse.  They download selfeshly and try every which way to make their downloads faster, capping their upload ect.  These guys I can live without, but I shall let them live...........for now.

3rd:  White hats, this category is the one people should want to be in.  These guys/girls never cap their upload, or just a little bit but still upload modestly.  These are good people (but they are still downloading illegally, who cares though?) and should be praised by what they do.
